<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="900">1.3. Applying the sales price to products</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Sales prices are linked to <a href="/en/item/introduction/structure">individual variations</a>, rather than to the item as a whole.
For example, if you sell a t-shirt in S, M, L and XL, then you can decide whether the XL variation should be a bit more expensive than the rest.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There are a few different ways to link sales prices to variations and enter the actual monetary prices:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>If you only want to save prices <em>for a few items</em>, then it makes sense to <a href="/en/item/managing-items#240">manually link sales prices and enter monetary amounts</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you want to save prices <em>for lots of items</em>, then we would recommend <a href="/en/item/import-export-create/import#800">importing the sales prices and monetary amounts</a>.
Alternatively, you could also import this data with an <a href="/en/welcome/assistants">assistant</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Rather than manually entering the monetary amounts, you might want plentymarkets to <a href="/en/item/settings/prices#1000">automatically calculate them for you</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="1000">2. New price calculation (Beta)</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Let plentymarkets calculate your prices for you.
For example, start with the purchase price and then add transportation costs, storage costs and taxes.
Finally, add a 7% profit margin on top.
With plentymarkets, you decide how your prices should be calculated.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">When will the function be available?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This chapter describes the new price calculation, which was launched at the start of 2021.
When the function will become available depends on whether you have a Beta, Early or Stable system.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Beta</strong> = March 31st, 2021</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Early</strong> = April 7th, 2021</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Stable</strong> = April 14th, 2021</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There is also an old price calculation, which is no longer being developed and will be phased out in the future.
The old tool is <a href="/en/item/settings/prices#2300">described here</a>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<h3 id="_procedure" class="discrete">Procedure</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This function is configured in several different steps:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/settings/prices#1100">Create the necessary price calculations</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/settings/prices#2100">Apply the calculation to your products</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/settings/prices#2000">Check the error log and fix any problems</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1100">2.1. Creating a new price calculation</h3>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Price calculation</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-plus  "></i></span> <strong>Price calculation</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Customise the settings to meet your needs:</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p>Enter a distinct name for the calculation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Create your own formulas.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select decimal places and rounding behaviour for each target price.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="1200">2.1.1. Settings</h4>
<table id="table-pricecalculation-settings" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 20%;">
<col style="width: 80%;">
