                                <a class="nav-link" id="group-function-or-batch-processing-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#group-function-or-batch-processing" role="tab" aria-controls="group-function-or-batch-processing" aria-selected="false">Group function or batch processing</a>
                            </li></ul><div class="tab-content" id="tabContent"><div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="manually" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="manually-tab">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you only want to save the price calculation <em>for a few items</em>, then it makes sense to manually link the price calculation.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » [Open variation] » Tab: Settings » Area: Sales prices</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Choose a previously created <a href="/en/item/settings/prices#1000">price calculation</a> from the right drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Reload the item data record if needed. To do so, right-click on the item tab and then click on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-undo  "></i></span> <strong>Reload</strong>.<br>
→ The sales price and the automatically calculated monetary price will be displayed in the list.</p>
</li>
